div.p:
                    Sir: I have the honor to report that the Mufti of
                    Jerusalem arrived unexpectedly in Baghdad yesterday, thus joining a number of
                    the Palestine Arab leaders who have been filtering into this city recently and
                    who are reported to be as follows: 

Fauzi al-Qaoogchi
Commander-in-Chief of the Rebellion three years
                            ago;

Araif Abdul Razzak
Present Commander-in-Chief of the
                            Rebellion;

Shaikh Hassan Salama
Commanding Officer of the Southern Area of
                            the Rebellion;

Amin al Tamimi
Member of the Higher Arab Committee and Member of
                            the Palestine Delegation at the Round Table Conference at London;

Abdullah al Umari
Secretary of the Higher Arab Committee;

Jamal al Husseini
President of the Palestine Mission to
                            London

Jalil al Shaikh Hassan Abu Su’ood
Active proponent of the Arab
                            cause in Palestine;

Ishaaq Darwish
Active proponent of the Arab cause in
                            Palestine;

Musa al Alim
Prominent Palestine lawyer;

Khalid al Farah;

Wasif Kamal;

Hanna Khalaf.
